race.comment: NICCONIUM (5) has been thereabouts in all five runs this campaign and looks to be on the doorstep of a maiden victory. Gets the services of Lang in the irons and should be right there when the whips are cracking. The well-related ATOMIC TIME (8) (half to G2 winner The Pendragon) has placed two of three this campaign and will be ready to peak now fourth-up from the break. Looms as the main danger. FAR BEYOND (9) just missed the placings on debut and will have taken a lot from that race day experience. Can improve enough to take this out. UNIQUELY FAMOUS (12) is facing the starter for the first time but won't need to be a superstar to be competitive against this lot. Keep safe from the Waller yard.
